A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO CRISIS SERVICES.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION I. The legislature finds that Act 86, Session Laws
2 of Hawaii 2024, established a crisis intervention and diversion
3 services program within the department of health to expand
4 existing services and divert those with mental health issues to
5 appropriate health care services. This program, along with the
6 new behavioral health crisis center at the Iwilei resource
7 center, connects individuals, including those who are homeless
8 or at risk of homelessness, to appropriate crisis services and
9 other community resources. While these programs have proven
10 successful, often the scope of the programs is not enough to
11 cover all areas of the State.
12 The legislature further finds that homelessness is a
13 significant issue on Oahu, with a noticeable presence of
14 unsheltered individuals, some of whom suffer from issues
15 relating to drugs, alcohol, or mental illness and do not have
16 access to the appropriate services for help.
