1 Therefore, the purpose of this Act is to expand the crisis
2 intervention and diversion services program by establishing two
3 crisis intervention and diversion services sites on Oahu.
4 SECTION 2. Section 334-171, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
5 amended by amending subsection (a) to read as follows:
6 "(a) There shall be established within the department a
7 crisis intervention and diversion services program to redirect
8 persons experiencing mental health disorders [and] or co­
9 occurring mental health and substance use disorders, or both,
10 who are at risk for involvement, or currently involved, with the
11 criminal justice system to the appropriate health care system
12 and services. The program shall establish at least two crisis
13 intervention and diversion services sites on the island of Oahu;
14 provided that of the two sites on Oahu, one site shall be
15 located in an area for which data shows disproportionate numbers
16 of individuals with mental health disorders or co-occurring
17 mental health and substance use disorders, or both. The program
18 may include the use of intensive mobile treatment services. The
19 department shall collaborate with law enforcement agencies,
20 courts, mental health providers, and the community for the
21 execution and implementation of these services."
